        "rich_text_YahcjW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Intro",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Gold jewelry has always been admired as the symbol of beauty, luxury, and heritage. Only a few metals can match the prestige and charm that gold does. So when you come across a beautiful gold piece in a jewelry store with a '9kt' label, doubt arises: Is this truly real gold? </p><p>In this blog, let's break all myths and discover who should choose 9kt gold and why? </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_hJUXrV": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Does \"9kt\" Mean?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Does \"9kt\" Mean?</h2><p>The word karat (kt) means the purity of gold. It tells you the presence or absence of any other alloys that are added to make the gold strong. Pure gold, i.e., 24kt gold, is soft and malleable. It requires other alloys to be molded into durable jewelry. </p>",
            "custom_id": "9kt"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_DmpLzN": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Is 9kt Gold Truly 'Real' Gold? Breaking The Myths",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Is 9kt Gold Truly 'Real' Gold? Breaking The Myths</h2>",
            "custom_id": "real"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_TzcNNF": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Absolutely! The biggest myth around 9kt gold is that it is 'fake'. There is also a misconception that 9kt gold just has a gold plating. Let’s clear this misunderstanding once and for all - 9kt gold is legally classified as real with 37.5% gold. Gold plating is just an outer surface, but 9kt gold has gold parts throughout the jewelry. While 9kt gold has lesser purity compared to other karats, it is real gold jewelry with hallmark stamped guaranteeing that it is 37.5% gold. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_eHNrPn": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Choose 9kt Gold? Should You Be Worried About The Qualitiy?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Choose 9kt Gold? Should You Be Worried About The Qualitiy?</h2><p>The choice of 9kt gold is not about real vs. fake. The decision should be made based on lifetsyle, purpose, budget, and preference. There are multiple reasons why 9kt gold is an appealing choice. 9kt gold has a high percentage of other alloys, making it more resistant, scratch free and durable, making it a great choice for daily wear. It is more affordable than 18kt and 22kt gold, making it an affordable luxury. Whether you are looking for earrings gold or a gold pendant, it is a versatile choice for modern day designs equipped for signature daily wear jewelry. Just like other gold jewelry, 9kt gold jewelry is also available in different tones such as yellow gold, white gold and rose gold. The only difference is that the 9kt gold in yellow tone is a little paler when compared to gold of higher tones. </p><p>Ofcourse choosing a lesser karat gold has its trade offs. In some cultures, 18kt and 22kt gold are the norms for buying gold <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/all-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Rings\">rings</a> as high purity gold is a standard choice for wedding jewelry, traditions and is a symbol of prestige. None of these mean that 9kt gold is a poor choice, it is all about choosing what is comfortable. 9kt gold is gold designed for practicality and everyday wear.  </p>",
            "custom_id": "quality"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_MWLzcQ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Comparing Gold - 9kt vs 14kt, 18kt and 22kt </h2><p>To help you make an informed decision and to put facts into perspective, we thought to make it easier for you to make a side by side comparision of 9kt gold with other karats. </p>",
            "custom_id": "comparison"
          }
        }
